30 MONUMENTA HISTORICA GELTIOA

The first extract given below was written at Athens about 444 Rc. In it Herodotus makes the Danube rise near the city Pyrene. This gross error is not repeated in the second extract, which was written some years later at Thurii. Here we are told the Danube rises in the country of the Celts, who after the Cynetes are the last people in Western Europe. The Cynetes dwelt in the extreme south of PortugaLl and the Oelts consequently in circa B.c. 442 extended over the south of Europe from the Alps to modern Portugal. We
